ncorrect combination of branch-state logic with PR-status interpretation across modules; Integration is sufficient with controlled PR states. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: no explicit real infra requirement in text, no LLM dependency, no multi-step agent chain. REJECTION-GATE: System rejected because behavior does not say live API/repo is required.","test_description":"Integrate detector with fake PR-status provider returning open and merged states for ahead branches; verify classifier/output never emits `stale-no-pr` for those states, while identical branch conditions with no PR does emit it.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.67,"System":0.23,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Staleness detection remains correct across rebases or squash merges where commit hashes change but branch state should no longer be classified as unPRed stale work.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"BEHAVIOR-QUOTE-GATE escalation phrase: \"across rebases or squash merges where commit hashes change\". REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: these are real VCS operations whose semantics frequently diverge from simplified fakes; real git history transformations are needed to catch true failures. REJECTION-GATE: Agentic/Workflow rejected because no AI decision steps are involved.","test_description":"Create real git branches and perform actual rebase and squash-merge sequences, then run staleness detection end-to-end. Assert branch is no longer classified as unPR'ed stale when effective changes are integrated despite hash rewrites.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
